Key Match Events: Yoshinobu Yamamoto pitched five scoreless innings in Game 5
The Padres were hitless in their final 19 at-bats of the series
San Diego did not score in the final 24 innings of the series
Pre-Game Insights: Andrew Friedman emphasized the importance of the bullpen passing the baton to one another
Dave Roberts compared the series' intensity to the Dodgers' 2020 NLCS against the Braves and even the 2004 Red Sox against the Yankees when he was a player
Post-Match Reflections: Kiké Hernández expressed pride in the team's resilience after the comeback win
Dave Roberts highlighted the victory as a pivotal moment in their playoff push
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers pitchers put up consecutive shutouts in the postseason for just the third time in franchise history
Shohei Ohtani ended his first postseason series just 4-for-20 (.200/.273/.350) with 10 strikeouts
